xgs360026fSystemTimeManualClockSource.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualClockSource
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualClockSource.description: default: 0, 0 : Use Local Settings, 1 : Use NTP Server.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualLocaltime.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualLocaltime
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualLocaltime.description: Get/Set the system time of the device. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute:Second'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43:05 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43:05 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59, Sec : 0 - 59.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset.description: Get/Set the NTP Time Zone. The value range is between -720 and 780 (minutes).

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time. The value range is between 1 and 1440 (minutes), Default : 60 (minutes).

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsBydatesFrom
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsBydatesTo
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the End time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringDayFrom
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Day From. 0 : Sun, 1 : Mon, 2 : Tue, 3 : Wed, 4 : Thu, 5 : Fri, 6 : Sat.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringWeekFrom
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Week From. 1 : first week, 2, 3, 4, 5 : last week

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringMonthFrom
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Month From. 1 : Jan, 2 : Feb, 3 : Mar, 4 : Apr, 5 : May, 6 : Jun, 7 : Jul, 8 : Aug, 9 : Sep, 10 : Oct, 11 : Nov, 12 : Dec.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringTimeFrom
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Hour:Minute'. ex: 05:43. The value range: Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringDayTo
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Day To. 0 : Sun, 1 : Mon, 2 : Tue, 3 : Wed, 4 : Thu, 5 : Fri, 6 : Sat.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringWeekTo
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Week To. 1 : first week, 2, 3, 4, 5 : last week

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringMonthTo
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Month To. 1 : Jan, 2 : Feb, 3 : Mar, 4 : Apr, 5 : May, 6 : Jun, 7 : Jul, 8 : Aug, 9 : Sep, 10 : Oct, 11 : Nov, 12 : Dec.

xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringTimeTo
xgs360026fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Hour:Minute'. ex: 05:43. The value range: Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360026fSystemTimeNTPIndex.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeNTPIndex
xgs360026fSystemTimeNTPIndex.description: The index of the ntp entry.

xgs360026fSystemTimeNTPServer.name: xgs360026fSystemTimeNTPServer
xgs360026fSystemTimeNTPServer.description: Get/Set the NTP Time Server1. You can use the IP address or domain name.

xgs360026fSystemAccountUserCreate.name: xgs360026fSystemAccountUserCreate
xgs360026fSystemAccountUserCreate.description: default: 0 0 : None (read only) 1 : Create a user account

xgs360026fSyslogLevel.name: xgs360026fSyslogLevel
xgs360026fSyslogLevel.description: default: 6 (Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

xgs360026fGetCommunity.name: xgs360026fGetCommunity
xgs360026fGetCommunity.description: Get/Set the get-community of the SNMP.

xgs360026fSetCommunityMode.name: xgs360026fSetCommunityMode
xgs360026fSetCommunityMode.description: Get/Set the set-community mode of the SNMP. default : 1, 0: disable, 1: enable.

xgs360026fSetCommunity.name: xgs360026fSetCommunity
xgs360026fSetCommunity.description: Get/Set the set-community of the SNMP.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfTable.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfTable
xgs360026fTrapHostConfTable.description: A list of trap host entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of xgs360026fTrapHostConfNumber.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfEntry.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfEntry
xgs360026fTrapHostConfEntry.description: This is the entry information for trap host.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfIndex.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfIndex
xgs360026fTrapHostConfIndex.description: The index of the trap host entry.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfVersion.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfVersion
xgs360026fTrapHostConfVersion.description: The version of the Trap PDU. Version : 2(SNMPv2c), 3(SNMPv3)

xgs360026fTrapHostConfIPType.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfIPType
xgs360026fTrapHostConfIPType.description: Server IP Type. Default: 4, 4 : IPv4, 6 : IPv6.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfIP.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfIP
xgs360026fTrapHostConfIP.description: This is the IP of the trap host.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfPort.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfPort
xgs360026fTrapHostConfPort.description: This is the receiving-port number of the trap host. range : 1 - 65535.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfCommunity.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfCommunity
xgs360026fTrapHostConfCommunity.description: The community/security name for the trap PDU.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel
xgs360026fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel.description: The Severity Level. 0 : Emerg, 1 : Alert, 2 : Crit, 3 : Error, 4 : Warning, 5 : Notice, 6 : Info, 7 : Debug.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel
xgs360026fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel.description: The Security Level, NoAuthNoPriv, AuthNoPriv, and AuthPriv. 1 : NoAuthNoPriv, 2 : AuthNoPriv, 3 : AuthPriv. Privacy protocol will be configured as 'DES' automatically if security level is 3(AuthPriv).

xgs360026fTrapHostConfAuthPtc.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfAuthPtc
xgs360026fTrapHostConfAuthPtc.description: Authentication Protocol, there are SHA and MD5 supported presently. 1 : MD5, 2 : SHA.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfAuthPassword.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfAuthPassword
xgs360026fTrapHostConfAuthPassword.description: Authentication Password, is used for authenticating. The return value is always '********'. If the authentication protocol is MD5, the length of password should be 8 ~ 32 characters. If the authentication protocol is SHA, the length of password should be 8 ~ 40 characters.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfPrivPtc.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfPrivPtc
xgs360026fTrapHostConfPrivPtc.description: This is the Privacy Protocol, which is used in AuthPriv. Only supports DES. An empty string will be returned if the security level is not 3(AuthPriv). 1 : DES.

xgs360026fTrapHostConfPrivPassword.name: xgs360026fTrapHostConfPrivPassword
xgs360026fTrapHostConfPrivPassword.description: The password is Privacy Key. The return value is always '********'. This Key must be more than 8 characters, and less than 32 characters.

xgs360026fPortConfCurrentSpeed.name: xgs360026fPortConfCurrentSpeed
xgs360026fPortConfCurrentSpeed.description: The current link speed of the port.

xgs360026fPortConfSpeed.name: xgs360026fPortConfSpeed
xgs360026fPortConfSpeed.description: default: 1, 0: disable state, 1: auto, 2: 10 Half, 3: 10 Full, 4: 100 Half, 5: 100 Full, 6: 1G full, only 'Dual Media' port have 7-11 option. Dual Media port default: 7, 7: SFP_Auto_AMS, 8: 100FX_AMS, 9: 1000X_AMS, 10: 100FX, 11: 1000X

xgs360026fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode.name: xgs360026fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode
xgs360026fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode.description: default: 0, Excessive Collision Mode : 0: Discard, 1: Restart, 2: not support.

xgs360026fPortConfPowerControl.name: xgs360026fPortConfPowerControl
xgs360026fPortConfPowerControl.description: default: 0, PowerControl : 0: disable, 1: Actiphy, 2: Dynamic (perfectReach), 3: Enable, 4: not support.

xgs360026fPortConfDescription.name: xgs360026fPortConfDescription
xgs360026fPortConfDescription.description: Interface specific description. Up to 47 characters describing this interface.

xgs360026fGARPStatisticsTable.name: xgs360026fGARPStatisticsTable
xgs360026fGARPStatisticsTable.description: Show the basic GARP port statistics.

xgs360026fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC.name: xgs360026fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC
xgs360026fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC.description: Peer MAC is MAC address of the neighbour Switch from with GARP frame is received.

xgs360026fMirrorMode.name: xgs360026fMirrorMode
xgs360026fMirrorMode.description: default: 0 0: disable 1: enable 2: rx only 3: tx only Setting Tx mirroring for analyzer port has no effect. Tx mirroring ignored

xgs360026fACLPortsConfPortRedirect.description: default: 0 0: Disable range : 0 - end port number

xgs360026fACLPortsConfCounter.name: xgs360026fACLPortsConfCounter
xgs360026fACLPortsConfCounter.description: Counts the number of frames that match this ACE.

xgs360026fACLACECreate.name: xgs360026fACLACECreate
xgs360026fACLACECreate.description: default: 0 0 : None (read only) 1 : Create an ACE entry

xgs360026fACLACEID.name: xgs360026fACLACEID
xgs360026fACLACEID.description: If the ACE ID is specified and an entry with this ACE ID already exists, the ACE will be modified. Otherwise, a new ACE will be added. range : 1 - 256.

xgs360026fACLACENextID.name: xgs360026fACLACENextID
xgs360026fACLACENextID.description: If the next ACE ID is non zero, the ACE will be placed before this ACE in the list. If the next ACE ID is zero, the ACE will be placed last in the list. range : 0 - 256.

xgs360026fACLACEIngressPort.name: xgs360026fACLACEIngressPort
xgs360026fACLACEIngressPort.description: Indicates the ingress port of the ACE. Possible values are: All: The ACE will match all ingress port. Port: The ACE will match a specific ingress port.Format: 1,3,6.

xgs360026fACLACEFrameType.name: xgs360026fACLACEFrameType
xgs360026fACLACEFrameType.description: 0: any, 1: arp, 2: etype, 3: icmp, 4: ipv4, 5: tcp, 6: udp.

xgs360026fACLACEDenyPortRedirect.name: xgs360026fACLACEDenyPortRedirect
xgs360026fACLACEDenyPortRedirect.description: Frames that hit the ACE are redirected to the port number specified here. Disabled: indicates that the port redirect operation is disabled. Port Format: 1,3,6.

xgs360026fACLACELogging.name: xgs360026fACLACELogging
xgs360026fACLACELogging.description: default: 0, 0: disable - Frames matching the ACE are not logged. 1: enable - Frames matching the ACE are stored in the system log.

xgs360026fACLACEShutdown.name: xgs360026fACLACEShutdown
xgs360026fACLACEShutdown.description: default: 0, 0: disable - Port shut down is disabled for the AC. 1: enable - If a frame matches the ACE, the ingress port will be disabled.

xgs360026fACLACEVLANTagPriority.name: xgs360026fACLACEVLANTagPriority
xgs360026fACLACEVLANTagPriority.description: Specify the tag priority for this ACE. The tag priority can't be set when 802.1Q Tagged is disabled default: 8, 8: Any, range : 0 - 8

xgs360026fACLACEVLANVID.name: xgs360026fACLACEVLANVID
xgs360026fACLACEVLANVID.description: Specify the VLAN ID filter for this ACE. The vid can't be set when 802.1Q Tagged is disabled. default: 0, 0: Any - No VLAN ID filter is specified. range : 0 - 4094

xgs360026fACLACEEtherType.name: xgs360026fACLACEEtherType
xgs360026fACLACEEtherType.description: 0: Any - Any but excluding 0x0800(IPv4) 0x0806(ARP) and 0x86DD(IPv6). range : 0 or 1536(0x0600)- 65535(0xffff).

xgs360026fACLACESMAC.name: xgs360026fACLACESMAC
xgs360026fACLACESMAC.description: Configure source MAC address for this ACE. <mac-address>: A frame that hits this ACE matches this source MAC address value. Any: Don't care.

xgs360026fACLACEDMACType.name: xgs360026fACLACEDMACType
xgs360026fACLACEDMACType.description: DMAC Type. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: Broadcast - Frame must be broadcast. 2: Unicast - Frame must be unicast. 3: Multicast - Frame must be multicast. 4: mac address range : 0 - 4

xgs360026fACLACEDMAC.name: xgs360026fACLACEDMAC
xgs360026fACLACEDMAC.description: Configure destination MAC address for this ACE. <mac-address>: A frame that hits this ACE matches this destination MAC address value. Any: Don't care. Broadcast: Frame must be broadcast. Unicast: Frame must be unicast. Multicast: Frame must be multicast.

xgs360026fACLACEArpOpcode.name: xgs360026fACLACEArpOpcode
xgs360026fACLACEArpOpcode.description: Configure ARP opcode for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: arp. 2: rarp. 3: other. 4: No data. range : 0 - 3

xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply.name: xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply
xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply.description: Specify the available ARP/RARP opcode (OP) flag for this ACE. default: 2, 0: Frame must have ARP Reply or RARP Reply OP flag. 1: Frame must have ARP Request or RARP Request OP flag set. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac.name: xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac
xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their sender hardware address field (SHA) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP frames where SHA is not equal to the SMAC address. 1: ARP frames where SHA is equal to the SMAC address. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac.name: xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac
xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their target hardware address field (THA) settings. default: 2, 0: RARP frames where THA is not equal to the DMAC address. 1: RARP frames where THA is equal to the DMAC address. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsLength.name: xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsLength
xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsLength.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP hardware address length (HLN) and protocol address length (PLN) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the HLN is not equal to Ethernet(0x06) or the (PLN) is not equal to IPv4(0x04). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the HLN is equal to Ethernet (0x06) and the (PLN) is equal to IPv4(0x04). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsIp.name: xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsIp
xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsIp.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP hardware address space (HRD) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the HLD is not equal to Ethernet(1). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the HLD is equal to Ethernet(1). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet.name: xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet
xgs360026fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP protocol address space (PRO) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the PRO is not equal to IP\n(0x800). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the PRO is equal to IP(0x800). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360026fACLACESIPType.name: xgs360026fACLACESIPType
xgs360026fACLACESIPType.description: Configure source IP address for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: IP Address. 2: No data. range : 0 - 1

xgs360026fACLACESIPIPAddress.name: xgs360026fACLACESIPIPAddress
xgs360026fACLACESIPIPAddress.description: A frame that hits this ACE matches this source IP address value.

xgs360026fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix.name: xgs360026fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix
xgs360026fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix.description: Network prefix. default: 32, 0: No data. range : 1 - 32

xgs360026fACLACEDIPType.name: xgs360026fACLACEDIPType
xgs360026fACLACEDIPType.description: Configure destination IP address for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: IP Address. 2: No data. range : 0 - 1

xgs360026fACLACEDIPIPAddress.name: xgs360026fACLACEDIPIPAddress
xgs360026fACLACEDIPIPAddress.description: A frame that hits this ACE matches this destination IP address value.

xgs360026fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix.name: xgs360026fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix
xgs360026fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix.description: Network prefix. default: 32, 0: No data. range : 1 - 32

xgs360026fACLACEIPProtocol.name: xgs360026fACLACEIPProtocol
xgs360026fACLACEIPProtocol.description: Configure IP protocol for this ACE. default: 256, 256: Any - Don't care. 257: No data. range : 0 - 256
